            "title": "ARTIST TECHNIQUES",
            "subtitle": "",
            "text": "Chaquira charms are made with hand-carved wooden figurines, where the beads are glued one by one with an adhesive. This technique is very time-consuming but allows for beautifully intricate designs. Maurilio is part of artisan conferences where different practices are shared with the goal to educate, promote, and preserve traditions.",
